						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">3gengames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Something like:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">NMI:<br />PHA<br />LDA $2002<br />INC Frame<br />PLA<br />RTI<br /></div></div><br />You can make this a bit shorter though:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">NMI:<br />BIT $2002<br />INC Frame<br />RTI</div>
<br />Yes, this is a valid way to handle NMIs, and prevents mapper writes from colliding, but it does introduce problems in case of lag frames. If the game loop takes longer than a frame to complete, not only the gameplay will slow down, but also the music/sfx, and raster effects (such as status bars) will glitch up.</div>

